# MDT Admin Password 


  <div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">This setting alone won't protect you. </div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin-left: .375in; margin: 0in;">SkipAdminPassword=YES</div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">You should also include this one. </div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin-left: .375in; margin: 0in;">AdminPassword=YourPassword</div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;"><br /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">However, there is another way, if you don't want to set all your deployed computer with same password:- </div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;"><br /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">When you create the installation TS, one of the step is to set Admin Password.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">&nbsp;<img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div><div style="margin: 0in;"></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">This admin password will be the local admin password for all deployments with that task sequence. I have so far found it in the following 2 places. </div><div style="margin: 0in;"><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;"><br /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">There is once I changed the bottom one without change the AutoLogon one, and the TS stopped in the middle, prompting for password. </div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;"><br /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">"Help" for "AdministratorPassword" shows:</div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin-left: .375in; margin: 0in;">To configure a blank administrator password, write an empty string in Windows System Image Manager (Windows&nbsp;SIM) by right-clicking on the Value setting, and choose <span style="font-weight: bold;">Write Empty String</span>. The built-in administrator account will be enabled with a blank password.</div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">It seems OK to set them empty, but when I actually set both of them to "Empty String", the TS stopped asking to set it. </div><div style="margin: 0in;"><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div><div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">After I change both of them to the same <span style="font-weight: bold;">non-Empty String</span>, it start to work perfectly. </div>
